physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Cervical range of motion was restricted by approximately 30–40% with moderate pain. Temporal artery appeared tortuous on the right, with nonpalpable pulse on the right and feeble on the left. Palpation of bilateral sternocleidomastoid muscles reproduced pain approximately 50–60%. TMJ palpation elicited mild pain of 3 on VAS bilaterally. Fibromyalgia screening was positive.
